originalText.text: Babs is my new favorite store in the East Village. It has such an eclectic mix of home goods, including photo prints, vintage glassware (cocktails!), and bath products with a really homey touch. It's clear the store focuses on upcycled and local products and I love the rotating gallery wall that features NYC-based artists. Excellent spot to grab a holiday gift or a special treat for yourself any time of year.

originalText.text: INCREDIBLE little store that I'm so happy is in the neighborhood. truly unique, I feel like I see a lot of things in there that I don't see anywhere else. owner is also really impressive and creative, she makes several things that she sells in there (like cheese-shaped candles, my favorite!!)

originalText.text: Babs is the best! Such a great place to shop around.  I went here on my visit to the city and was very impressed with their selection of home decor, jewelry and unique gifts. The owner was so welcoming and helpful in finding a perfect NYC keepsake. if youre like me and love to support local shops and local artists, Babs is the perfect stop!

originalText.text: Shopping at Babs made buying a bag of coffee feel special. When I arrived home it felt like I was unboxing a surprise for myself —that’s how thoughtfully curated the store feels. Don’t sleep on the pantry items! They have the most delicious treats.
